Technical Curriculum Engineering Lead
San Francisco, CA | New York City, NY | Seattle, WA
About Anthropic
Anthropic’s mission is to create reliable, interpretable, and steerable AI systems. We want AI to be safe and beneficial for our users and for society as a whole. Our team is a quickly growing group of committed researchers, engineers, policy experts, and business leaders working together to build beneficial AI systems.

About the Role
Anthropic is pioneering safe and reliable AI assistants. As we continue to advance industry-leading language models, we aim to empower users worldwide to build trustworthy and reliable generative AI applications.

We are seeking an exceptional senior technical education expert to spearhead frontier content development and experimental education to empower developers to build with and on the broad spectrum of Claude's capabilities. You will explore new approaches to technical education, creating innovative demos, tutorials, and cookbooks that showcase cutting-edge Claude implementations. Working at the intersection of our research advances and developer needs, you will translate complex frontier concepts into digestible, practical education that inspires developers to push boundaries.

This role requires deep technical aptitude, experimental mindset, creative flair, and the ability to develop content that becomes the template for broader educational initiatives. If you love strategically defining how developers learn and master frontier technologies, exploring the bleeding edge of AI capabilities, and building inventive demonstrations of advanced features, this is the perfect opportunity for you.

Core Responsibilities:
Create first-of-their-kind educational content for Claude's capabilities, from basic fundamentals to frontier capabilities
Develop innovative prototypes, demos, and code samples that showcase Claude implementations at all technical levels
Partner closely with crossfunctional teams such as GTM, Partnerships, and Marketing to refine content and enable scaling across various formats
Design educational content templates and exemplars that other teams can learn from, adapt, and expand for different use cases
Work alongside product and research teams to transform technical features into accessible learning modules
Test and iterate on novel educational approaches, gathering feedback to continuously refine your methods
Establish quality standards for technical content that can be applied across the education ecosystem
Create educational pathways that guide developers from basic implementations to sophisticated, cutting-edge usage
Influence product decisions by highlighting developer and technical user learning needs
Drive strategic decision-making around how developers learn and interact with Claude, helping steer and inform Anthropic’s broader user education strategy
You may be a good fit if you:
Have 8+ years of relevant technical education experience with a focus on developer and technical audiences
Excel at creating innovative, multimedia educational content that makes technical concepts accessible to developers
Have developed technical cookbooks, code examples, or tutorials that have influenced developer adoption
Can translate technical concepts into practical, hands-on learning experiences for developers
Possess deep technical aptitude and can write elegant code exemplars demonstrating various implementation levels
Are comfortable with and excited to create content to teach foundational capabilities, bleeding-edge features, and frontier ML research that may never have been taught before
Have successfully partnered with developer relations or advocacy teams to scale educational impact
Are creative, curious, and constantly exploring new ways to educate and inspire technical audiences
Can balance experimental approaches with practical developer needs and learning objectives
Work seamlessly across teams to connect product capabilities with developer education
